7 An Act relating to state government; amending Section 1,
Chapter 425, O.S.L. 2024 (74 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section
8 2294.1), which relates to the Oklahoma Museum of Popular
Culture Supplemental Revolving Fund; and modifying determined
9 funds provided for expenditures.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 425, O.S.L.
14 2024 (74 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 2294.1), is amended to read as
15 follows:
16 Section 2294.1. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a
17 revolving fund for the Oklahoma Historical Society, to be designated
18 the "Oklahoma Museum of Popular Culture Supplemental Revolving
19 Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal
20 year limitations, and shall consist of all monies received by the
21 Oklahoma Historical Society from appropriations of the Legislature
22 designated for deposit in this fund. All monies accruing to the
23 credit of the fund are hereby appropriated and shall be budgeted and
24 expended to provide funding for repairs, planning, staging,
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2673 Page 1
1 refu rbishments, and improvements to real and personal property, and
2 funding for construction of the Oklahoma Museum of Popular Culture.
3 No expenditures shall be made from the fund until the State
4 Treasurer determines that funds provided by local and county
5 governments, the federal government, or through monetary donations
6 or enforceable pledges for monetary donations in the amount of
7 Eighteen Million Dollars ($18,000,000.00) are made for repairs,
8 planning, staging, refurbishments, and improvements to real and
9 personal property, and funding for construction of the Oklahoma
10 Museum of Popular Culture; provided, no funds collected or received
11 prior to May 25, 2023 May 25, 2021, shall be counted toward the
12 amount. Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon warrants
13 issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
14 law with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
15 Services for approval and payment. On November 15, 2025, if no
16 determination is made by the State Treasurer pursuant to the
17 provisions of this section authorizing expenditures from this fund,
18 all unencumbered funds remaining in the Oklahoma Museum of Popular
19 Culture Supplemental Revolving Fund shall be transferred to the
20 State Treasurer for deposit in the General Revenue Fund of the State
21 Treasury for the fiscal year ending June 30, 2024.
